myurl <- "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/shakirovb/STA553/main/DATA/penguinuse.jpeg"
penguin2 <- read.csv("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/shakirovb/STA553/main/w02-penguins.csv")
library(scales)

z <- tempfile()
download.file(myurl,z,mode="wb")
pic <- readJPEG(z)
raster.penguin <- as.raster(pic)
bill<- penguin$bill_length_mm
flipper<- penguin$flipper_length_mm
species<- penguin$species
size<-penguin$body_mass_g
sizemg<-size/2000

## identifying the different species
Adelie.id = which(species=="Adelie")  # value are case sensitive!
Chinstrap.id = which(species=="Chinstrap")
Gentoo.id = which(species=="Gentoo")

## color code
col.code = c(alpha("red",0.5),alpha("skyblue2",0.5),alpha("salmon2",0.5))

## making an empty plot: type = "n" ==> no point,
plot(bill, flipper,main = " Flipper Length vs Bill length", type = "n", xlab="Bill length (mm)",ylab="Flipper length(mm)")


points(bill[Adelie.id], flipper[Adelie.id], pch = 19, col = col.code[1] ,cex=sizemg[Adelie.id])
points( bill[Chinstrap.id],flipper[Chinstrap.id], pch = 19,col = col.code[2],cex=sizemg[Chinstrap.id])
points( bill[Gentoo.id],flipper[Gentoo.id], pch = 19, col = col.code[3],cex=sizemg[Gentoo.id] )
legend("topleft", c("Adelie", "Chinstrap", "Gentoo"), 
                  col=c("red", "blue", "green"),
                  pch=c(19, 19, 19))

#Position of the image through bottom-left and top-right Coordinates
rasterImage(raster.penguin,37,220,40,230)
text(50,172, "The size is proportional to Body Mass", col = "purple", cex = 0.5)
